column5: My Dad and I just got back from Jackon's Point after a full day on the ice.  The good news is we broke our ice fishing season skunk with a 5lb Whitefish, and numerous misses.  The bad news is we went to unpack the car and realized our bucket complete with several rod/reel combo's was missing .  I know it's a long shot, but I thought I would post here just in case an OFC'er came across it.  They were left just above the launch ramp at the end of the parking lot.  Thanks either way, guys.
Congrats on the whitefish. Bummer about the gear though.  I'll be at Innisfil tomorrow giving it one last shot.
I hope you are lucky enough to get them back.Not a good way to end a good day.Dan
good for you getting that nice whitefish,  but sorry to hear about your ice fishing gear..  ..i dont think the odds are very good on getting the stuff back,but ya never know....good luck
